You can use either of the following methods to mount Gluster volumes:

*
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:_Manually_Mounting_Volumes_Using_NFS[Manually
Mounting Volumes Using NFS]
*
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:_Automatically_Mounting_Volumes_Using_NFS[Automatically
Mounting Volumes Using NFS]

*Prerequisite*: Install nfs-common package on both servers and clients
(only for Debian distribution), using the following command:

$ sudo aptitude install nfs-common

After mounting a volume, you can test the mounted volume using the
procedure described in
http://www.gluster.org/community/documentation/index.php/Gluster_3.2:_Testing_Volumes_Mounted_Using_NFS[Testing
Volumes Mounted Using NFS].

